# CloudTrail — who did what

Records **every API call**: console, CLI, SDK, service-to-service. Five fields per event:

- **Who** — IAM principal · **What** — the action (`PutObject`, `DeleteTrail`)
- **When** — timestamp · **Where** — IP, agent, region · **Result** — success / error + params

The audit trail behind every *"who did that?"*.

## Event types

| Type | Captures | Default | Cost |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Management** | control-plane, IAM, network | **on, free** | 1st copy free |
| **Data** | S3 GetObject, Lambda Invoke | opt-in | charged |
| **Insights** | ML anomalies in API volume | opt-in | charged |

## Getting it right

- **Multi-region trail → S3** = the baseline (every region, one place)
- **Log file validation** + **S3 Object Lock** → tamper-proof (attackers call `DeleteTrail` first)
- Trail → **CloudWatch Logs** → alarm on root login / sensitive calls
